          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRIMP"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Heavy Ion Research Facility in",
                "                Lanzhou (HIRFL)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The collimated 9Be beam with an initial energy of",
                "50.4 MeV was delivered by HIRFL. The average beam",
                "current was about 13 enA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Five targets of 89Y, each with thickness of about 1",
                "mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA",
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A stacked foil online activation",
                "followed by an offline gamma-ray spectroscopy method.",
                "After the 12 hours irradiation, the gamma activity of",
                "the targets was measured offline using five HPGe",
                "detector groups."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A high-precision current integrator was",
                "employed to measure the beam flux deposited at the",
                "Faraday cup, placed after the target. In order to",
                "repel the secondary electrons, the Faraday cup was",
                "biased with a negative 400 V electrode on the",
                "collector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two silicon surface- barrier detectors were",
                "mounted at +-30 deg to the beam direction for",
                "monitoring the elastic scattering of the 9Be",
                "projectiles by an thin Au foil placed upstream from",
                "the target stack."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Each HPGe detector group consisted of two HPGe",
                "detectors were positioned 180 deg to each other. The",
                "data acquisition system was set such that single",
                "gamma-ray and gamma-gamma coincidence measurements",
                "could be performed simultaneously. The Ge crystal",
                "part of each detector was surrounded by a Pb annular",
                "cylinder of 3 cm thickness to reduce background from",
                "natural radioactivity. The energy calibration and",
                "absolute efficiency of the detectors was determined",
                "using a set of activity calibrated radioactive",
                "sources (60Co, 133Ba, and 152Eu) placed with the same",
                "geometry as the targets."
              ]
            }
          ],
